SIMPLE: lituus
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lituus
<hw>Lit"u*us</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Litui</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Rom. Antig.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A curved staff used by the
augurs in quartering the heavens.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>An instrument
of martial music; a kind of trumpet of a somewhat curved form and shrill
note.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Math.)</fld> <def>A spiral whose polar equation is
<mathex>r<exp>2</exp>⟦theta⟧ = a</mathex>; that is, a curve the square
of whose radius vector varies inversely as the angle which the radius
vector makes with a given line.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Livable</ent>⟦br⟧
